    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini Dei et salvatoris nostri Iesu Christi. Concessimus nos <rs
                            key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis">gloriosissimus</rs> domnus Grimoald,
                        summus <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux</rs> gentis Longobardorum, tibi Iohanni,
                            <rs key="#Abbots">abbati</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Casalia #Coloni/tenants"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1900">Christi martiris Vincencii</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>, <rs key="#Casalia">casalem</rs>
                        nomine <geogName
                            key="#Casalia #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Coloni/tenants"
                            ref="#estates/1908">Casa Summi</geogName>, qui fuit de <persName
                            key="#Coloni/tenants"><name ref="Vitalianus">Vitaliano</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">colono</rs> nostro, quatenus ab hac die habeatis
                        et possideatis, et a nullo quemquam homine numquam habeatis aliquam
                        questionem aut reprehensionem, sed, sicut superius diximus, perpetuis
                        temporibus securi valeatis possidere ipsum supranominatum casale. Quam vero
                        membrana concessionis dictavi ego <persName
                            key="#Subdeacons #Professional_writer"><name ref="Wizo"
                            >Vuiso</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Subdeacons">subdiaconus,</rs> ex iussione suprascripte potestatis,
                        tibi <persName key="#Notary"><name ref="Pergoaldus"
                            >Pergoaldo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notario</rs> scribendum. <date>Actum <placeName
                                key="#Palatium" ref="#places/110">Benevento</placeName>, in <rs
                                key="#Palatium">palacio</rs>, mense augusti, per indiccione
                            prima</date>, feliciter.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>CV I, n. 67, pp. 319-320; CDL IV/2, n. 46, pp. 154-157; Voigt 1902: n. 29</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p>Zielinski 2003: 127-128</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="links">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>This document is a transcript of an authentic preceptum from the ducal period of
                    the chancery of Benevento and contains mutilations and interpolations. The
                    interpolations refer to the names of Prince Grimoald and Abbot John. According
                    to Zielinski,  the praeceptum may have been issued by Arechis and date back to
                    763, during the abbacy of John I (CDL VI/2, p. 156).</p>
            </div>
